<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Live Patient Monitor</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/mistexamples.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/patientmonitor.css">
</head>
<body>
    <main class="container">
        <a href="/MistExamples" class="back-link">← Back to Examples</a>
        
        <header class="mb-4">
            <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">InstanceComponent</span>
            <h1 style="margin-top: 0;">Live Patient Monitor</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="patient-grid">
            #for(context in contexts):
                #extend("PatientMonitorExample/PatientComponent")
            #endfor
        </section>
        
        <div class="mt-4">
            <p class="desc">
                A high-stakes demonstration of 
                <span class="inline-code">InstanceComponent</span> 
                joining two disparate data sources: 
                <span class="inline-code" style="color: #909296">Patient Identity</span> 
                (Stable/EMR) and 
                <span class="inline-code" style="color: #37b24d">Live Vitals</span> 
                (Transient/Telemetry).
                Each card is a unified view of two separate database tables joined by a shared UUID.
            </p>
        </div>
    </main>
    
    <script src="/morphdom.js"></script>
    <script src="/mist.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
